  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, I have taken into consideration several mitigating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating this is an isolated incident rather than a pattern of criminal behavior. Furthermore, the defendant has already made efforts to partially repay the stolen funds, demonstrating remorse and a willingness to make amends. While a period of incarceration is necessary to serve as a deterrent and to penalize the violation of fiduciary duty, a lengthy term is unwarranted given the circumstances. Therefore, a modest sentence of 6 months of incarceration is appropriate, which should be followed by a probationary period focused on full restitution of the remaining balance.",
